set-bg: img/background/andrea.jpg

= 1983, The Phantasm

{!<div class="typewriter dialogue6">!}

Andrea. 

Oh Andrea. She never gave up on anyone, did she?

She had no reason to trust you when you came back from Tibet. The two of you hadn’t spoken in years. For all she knew, you were destined to become another nepotistic playboy who did nothing but spend his parents fortune on hedonism and hookers. You insisted that any support was optional. You did have a reason to leave Gotham, leave before you graduated, and even leave you. A part of you wishes you never did. But still, she chose to reach out again. Her embrace after miles of separation between space and time never left your heart. 

You didn’t know it back then, but it was then where you first fell in love with the girl who never let you go. 

You couldn’t let her go. Yanking her arm, you beg her to stop. To not let the death of her father end like this. She couldn’t get her revenge.

So then, you let the Red Hood go. 

Now, by his own fault, he’s gone, face, body burned by acid.

And yet the pain remains. It’s a silence she was longing for, and now that it was here, it was the last thing anyone wanted.

You can see it in the blue of her eyes. Betrayal. You knew from the moment she told you that some escape justice, the same that will kill, that will destroy, that will break again, with justice powerless to stop them; that someone needs to intervene, to be justice in their stead.

You are no executioner. Yet Andi was prepared to act in your stead. Not just to be a judge or enforcer, but become the reaper herself. She can’t see her heart is clouding her judgement. That no amount of killing within ever truly grants fulfillment. That this all is just a mirage in the desert.

She doesn’t see the patience, only someone that wishes to stop her from doing what is right, what is just. The person who she always stood back to back, turning against hers. You don’t blame Andi. Fault doesn’t just come from her. She can’t be at fault from wishing justice, in a world as cruel as this one.

You loved her once. Some part of you still does. If only the same road didn't drive the two of you in completely different directions. If only you didn’t abandon her when she needed it the most. 

Now, she’s ready to go on her own, to find herself while you do the same. You may not see each other again for years, maybe even for the rest of your life. But there's something lingering within the thoughts of your first love…

{!</div>!}

- @phantasm_feeling: We’re out of touch, out of touch with ourselves, with each other. Still, I have hope time will bring what each of us needs. One day, we’ll find a middle where we will see each other.
- @phantasm_order: We knew each other well, just not well enough. What we learned pulled us closer, what we now know is driving us apart. I hope she finds herself, but I don’t think we can reconcile. I can’t let my emotions drive me to ignore what I would never allow for anyone else.
- @phantasm_liberty: I can’t let a white lie hide what broke. She would have broken the life of another if it sounded like the right decision to her. Perhaps she will see the wrong in that decision in the future, yet I can’t let it linger. No one has any right to the life of another.

@phantasm_feeling
