new-page: true

{!<div class="typewriter">!}

= The Demon's Heir

Gotham was always your home, yet your business takes you all across the globe. In the dusty streets of Shanghai, Waynecorp is one of the first to reach an open pearl, but certainly not the last. Your hotel reeks of extravagance, nothing like the carved out remote palace you lived in the last time you came to this country. You’re flipping through an issue of Times, something you’d never thought you’d say before the hotel phone blares out of nowhere. You pick up, and hear the voice of someone you’d never forget. 

“Wayne. You’re here, correct?”

His daughter. The daughter of the demon. You call out her name.

“Talia. Talia Al Ghul, yes. Wayne, I understand your circumstances at this given moment, but if you have time to spare, I’d like to speak to you in person. I have quite urgent news. Please be there, Wayne.”

You wait at a local shengjian bao stand. The one right next to the hotel. By the glances given at your direction, you stand out like a sore thumb ordering food in fluent Mandarin, waiting for your meal like you’re waiting for a date. In a way you are, you suppose. Finally, she arrives. The two of you sit on flimsy stools, and she seems just happy to be there. To be with a friend again.

“How is the city of Gotham like, Wayne?” 

You lean in forward, hand resting against your chin. Dangerous as always. That’s why it needs me, to push the city forward, not back. 

“Your determination was always admirable, Wayne. Perhaps you can take my father and I to visit one day.” 

Maybe. But you have a feeling her dad prefers the grand peaks of Tibet over the bustling metro of Gotham. Ms. Al Ghul, with her posture as straight as a soldier’s, is unfazed by your remarks. 

“Perhaps, then, it will have to be the two of us. You’ve seen my hometown, I would like to visit yours. See how the man who my father praises so highly was formed. Perhaps, just this once.” 

You tilt your head to the side. Your stomach growls smelling scents of freshly grilled pork buns. Ah, remind me then, when is our serving going to arrive? 

She looks down. Then, the daughter of the demon effortlessly scans her surroundings. She stands up, and alerts the stand operator of their tardiness. Soon enough, she places the container of buns right on the egg cart right between you two. 

“It is quite fortunate that he was finished with our order the moment I had asked him about it.” 

She then tosses a pair of chopsticks into the air and you just barely catch it as she splits hers in two with effortless force. She dips her bao in vinegar. You’re about to go condimentless on yours before she alerts you to the other dipping tray she brought with the order. 

“The soy sauce is for you, laowai.” 

Your face is flushed with embarrassment. You didn’t think she’d remember. You and Talia gobble down your evening snack, talking about nothing in particular. For just a second, the two of you feel like teenagers again. As you snag the last bun from the grasp of her chopsticks, making sure to eat it as obnoxiously slow as possible. After that, you’re ready to call it quits. You push away your stool, ready to leave before she uncharacteristically blurts something out.

“Wayne. Bruce Wayne. There is something I must tell you.”

She switches from Mandarin to English. Her stoic eyebrows furl in concentration.

“My father and I are raising a child.” 

“Who’s the father?”

She glances around. The Shanghainese don’t understand a lick of what she’s saying. You’re not sure if that’s a good or a bad thing. Talia takes a deep breath in.

“You. You are the father. There was no rape, nothing remotely as such, but beyond that I cannot explain further, but that is the truth.”

{!</div>!}

- @talia_bullshit: You’re bullshiting me. There’s no way that this could theoretically work, let alone practically! What did you do, take my - no, I don’t even want to know. Talia, you betrayed me!
- @talia_here: I’m here for you. I don’t know what’s going on, but whatever you’re dealing with, I will be there. For both you, and our child.
- @talia_idk: That’s a lot to take in. I’m not sure how to feel about this. I need some time, I’m sorry. 

