{!<div class="typewriter">!}

= The Catwoman Rips your Cowl

Most criminals were one and done. It’s not rare for someone to escape their first crime. It’s rarer if they escape their second. It becomes notable when they escape it thrice. After that, the numbers become less meaningful. It’s less a statistic, it’s more of a myth. 

There was one such criminal that escaped you 3 times already. The Catwoman. The greatest thief of gotham city, responsible for the sudden unfortunate disappearance of multiple private collections of arts and jewelry. 

The Jewels and metal made sense to be resold, but why from the hardest places to take them from? And the art… There was nothing that seemed to co-relate to a clear buyer for any of them. Either she had perfect execution and no long term plan, her plans were unknown or… She’s simply yearning for the challenge.

Trying to catch Catwoman felt more like a chase. A thrill, a hunt rather than a fight. This is how she liked it after all.

Another night went and this time, you managed to catch her before she could fade in the night. New diamonds sparkling brighter than streetlights hung around her arm.

You jumped out from one building to the other, two shadows dancing on roofs, a flash with each hop, a drum with each step.

Suddenly, you flew, you heard a snap. You felt your grappling hook fail you for the first time. All became dark.

“Have you ever danced with the Devil in the pale moonlight?”

Eyes open, back against the ground. You had failed. A rip between two roofs let you fall onto a narrow street, a miracle and preparations for such an event allowing you to breathe but…

You felt the wind on your face. Your mask has been on your face for so long, you had forgotten what it felt to have the rays of the moon cool your skin.

“You’re a bad dancer… Bruce.”

You reflexively put your hand on your face. Some blood falling over your fingers. The feline shadow came into view as you try to stand on your feet. As she came to finish her work? She has taken everything after all.

“I’m surprised you’re doing all of this out of all people, you know?  Risking your life for the sake of others… You’ve blown me way out of my expectations…”

Adrenaline seeps through your veins. You gulp, bracing for the worst. A spotlight, a camera flash. 

“But I don’t want this night to end this way, not just yet.”

Steps came closer, their noise throwing you against the wall. Yet, throwing out her whips to the ground, throwing diamonds and jewels. She was not cornering you. Her hands drawing on her face, pulling out the face of Selina Kyle.

The voice didn’t feel quite right up until now, but it couldn’t be anyone else. The head of the most successful investment firm of the city… Stealing? Those certainly had value but she had no need to take them for herself.

“You don’t know how many cops have tried to catch me in the act since I first started, Batman. It’s like they’re personally offended by me just existing, by me getting away every single time.”

This wasn’t a gloat. Even towering over you, none of this imbalance was abused in her words.

“But you, you never wavered. You could’ve just shot the damn bitch before she escapes again, you know, Batsy? But you didn’t. You play fair, but you’re a rebel in the books. You always get knocked down, and yet you always get back up again. You’re an oxymoron, Bruce. I like that about you. You’re the thrill I want.”

“There’s no other man in this town that I've trusted more than you, Batman. This hunt isn’t over. One to one, I want you to trust me. Trust my name to you as you gave yours to mine.”

Slowly, this mask would fall back onto her face, taking back her whip, a wink and a swing into the night.

She gave you this night to you.

{!</div>!}

- @catwoman_open: I do not know all the games she plays, but those seem not as mortal. I’ll talk more with Selina, with Catwoman. This is not an edge she wishes to fall down from. I know she will be better.
- @catwoman_villain: I think she may be much more naïve than she claims to be. It may not come this year or the next, but eventually, she’ll be caught.

