{!<div class="typewriter">!}

= Reaction

After 4 years of rule, Hamilton Hill has little to show for it. At least, that’s what most media have been spewing ever since his inauguration.

In those 4 years, you’ve defeated the five families of Gotham, finally put the Joker behind bars, led to a never seen reduction in the crime rate of Gotham city and yet, people only think that the city has become more violent, more divided, more unsafe.

Some would say that Hamilton Hill is just riding your result, some will say that he should have done more, some others will say that the deck is stacked against them. However, isn’t that the excuse every politician uses?

Be that as it may, Hamilton Hill will join the choirs by touting the lines of law and order during his re-election attempt. This was not his terrain, not his culture, he got thrown out.

There's a new man in town, his name is Quincy Sharp. Tough as nails, tough on crime, tough on the sources of crimes, criminals. He’s giving an open hand to anyone that would help him, which include those that have previously fought against him.

You didn’t fully trust Hamilton Hill before, you’re not sure why you should trust Sharp either. He has a way of speaking that much more straight Hill ever was, however, if you can trust his words, can you trust who put those in his mouth? 

{!</div>!}

- @supportquincy: Whatever his political ideals or personality, I’ve much more to lose than to gain by staying silent. I will present an open palm to him.
- @dontsupportquincy: Don't support.

