{!<div class="typewriter">!}

= 1991, Jason's Capture and Death

Last night was tiring. Jason’s been missing for days. You have no clue where he went, let alone where to look. Before you panic further you receive a call. Gordon received a tape at the GCPD this morning. The Tape is black, with a white label taped to it. Drawn with a red marker, it’s a smiling face. 

You immediately fill with dread as you believe the worse has happened. At the batcave you analyze the video. You didn’t think he could be this cruel, this reprehensible. 

Jason. It couldn’t be. It’s hours of video, where he beats Jason to near death with a crowbar. Jason’s screams are something you can’t ever forget. It’s haunting. 

You have to stop him. This has gone too far. He was just a boy. What monster does that to a boy? 

{!</div>!}

@jason_menu

- @footage: Analyze the tape further and find the location.
- @find_joker: I need to find him, this ends tonight. I will put him behind bars and make sure he never ever gets out again
- @kill_joker: Kill Joker.

@footage 
subtitle: Maybe he's still alive.
view-if: jason_footage = 0
on-arrival: jason_footage = 1
go-to: jason_menu

You pry through the footage. He left no evidence to where this happened. Let alone where the body….. no, there isn’t a body. He’s alive…

@find_joker

You find Joker. Believe it or not he simply turns himself in, no fight, no theatrics. Nothing. He gives up. The two of you say nothing on the ride to Arkham. You can’t muster a word. And he’s already got his laughs in.

- @1993_start: Next year.

@kill_joker
choose-if: sanity == 0 or moral_compass == 0
unavailable-subtitle: No… that’s too far. I can’t bring myself. He’d only get what he wants. 

No. You did not do this.

- @find_joker: You went to find him.

