    introDialogue();
!}

{!<div class="typewriter">!}

Things have ran on for a long time. A decade fighting crime and somehow, it feels as if you’ve stepped in the place you’ve been when you first returned from Tibet.

Crime still fills the street, people still cheat, lie to one another, some starve while others overstuff themselves. And yet, here you are, a stranger now just another part of those moving pictures.

Time has only made you grow even more resentful of politicians than you were but a teenager. Once I found the hole, it just went all the way down. To were? Who knows.

This was rock bottom. You’ve found those abyss and they have stared back once again. They are judging you, all your actions, all your failures. You are even harsher to yourself than they’ll ever be. No one sees as many flaws as a mirror.

Yet, this duty is still called to you. You felt their hold, warm. You had to do it, for them. You had to break this cycle. No one will but you. Authors are happy with an eternally ongoing story that sees them always escape.

This book will see a chapter close. You have the pen, the ink. Was this what you wanted? How will you judge?

{!</div>!}



- @bruce: I inspired fear. It is time I inspire hope. My suit will serve better than my Cowl.
- @batman: This place of power is but a springboard for my duty to the city. Batman will no longer be bound.

